This astronomical computer was an innovation perfected by the Arabs during the tenth century. A golden colored disc with many different uses, including: navigation, telling time, calculating distances and discovering the positions of the planets. It was highly developed in the Islamic world, demonstrating creativity and originality – which is also the inspired essence of our café. The main use of an astrolabe was to navigate by the Sun and stars, proving an ability to see beyond what are right in front of you. name: Jordan Eco Park
bio:
Jordan EcoPark located in the northern part of the Jordan Valley (north of Jordan) covers an area of 27 square kilometers with diverse Mediterranean bushland ecosystem and it includes the Ziglab dam, which is the first dam in Jordan - established in the 1960s,   and it’s surrounded by farmland and Bedouin goat herders.  and it is considered a leading model for preserving ecologically important habitats in Jordan.   

Since the EcoPark is established, the wildlife has flourished and the locals and tourists alike have been able to spend more time there to enjoy the beauty of nature in the Jordan Valley. The park is a unique concept in Jordan and suitable for most age groups. It is a perfect get-away for families, youth, nature and adventures lovers.  

The EcoPark moves toward sustainability by focusing on:
· Ecological building
· The use of renewable energy
· Solar water heating system

· Community support

name: Jordan Trail
bio:
The Jordan Trail is a long distance hiking trail in Jordan connecting the length of Jordan from Um Qais in the north to Aqaba in the south. Offering 40 days of hiking over more than 650 kilometers of trail, and travelling through 52 villages and towns on its way. The trail traverses the diverse landscapes and vistas of the country, from the rolling wooded hills of the north, the rugged wadis and cliffs overlooking the Jordan Rift Valley, the rose rock of Petra, the dramatic sands and towering mountains in Wadi Rum, to the crystal waters of the Red Sea.

 

As you walk the Jordan Trail, it becomes a journey through the history of Jordan and an encounter with its diverse culture. Travelling the length of the country enables a chance to peel through the different layers of culture, to taste the varied cuisines of Jordan, encounter locals while walking and spending your nights in their home-stays. It is also an opportunity to learn the history of Jordan, the different civilizations who have made their marks on the land. The trail moves through major historical sites in the region such as Um Qais, Jerash, and Petra, while also harboring hidden ruins resting amongst the land.

name: Mujib Reserve
bio:
At 410 meters below sea level, the Mujib Biosphere Reserve is the lowest nature reserve on Earth. Its rugged and spectacular mountains border the Dead Sea coast and are dissected by several river-filled canyons that offer the best river and adventure hikes in Jordan. The breathtaking scenery and the challenge of negotiating Mujib’s fast-flowing rivers make the Reserve one of Jordan’s most popular natural attractions.

Mujib’s complex river system and all-year water flow enable it to support a rich biodiversity. To date, over 300 species of plants, 10 species of carnivores and numerous species of resident and migratory birds have been recorded. Some of the mountain and valley areas are difficult to reach and offer safe havens for rare species of cats, mountain goats (Ibex) and other mountain animals.

bio:

Since the EcoPark is established, the wildlife has flourished and the locals and tourists alike have been able to spend more time there to enjoy the beauty of nature in the Jordan Valley. The park is a unique concept in Jordan and suitable for most age groups. It is a perfect get-away for families, youth, nature and adventures lovers.

name: Jordan Trail
bio:
The Jordan Trail is a long distance hiking trail in Jordan connecting the length of Jordan from Um Qais in the north to Aqaba in the south. Offering 40 days of hiking over more than 650 kilometers of trail, and travelling through 52 villages and towns on its way. The trail traverses the diverse landscapes and vistas of the country, from the rolling wooded hills of the north, the rugged wadis and cliffs overlooking the Jordan Rift Valley, the rose rock of Petra, the dramatic sands and towering mountains in Wadi Rum, to the crystal waters of the Red Sea.

 

As you walk the Jordan Trail, it becomes a journey through the history of Jordan and an encounter with its diverse culture. Travelling the length of the country enables a chance to peel through the different layers of culture, to taste the varied cuisines of Jordan, encounter locals while walking and spending your nights in their home-stays. It is also an opportunity to learn the history of Jordan, the different civilizations who have made their marks on the land. The trail moves through major historical sites in the region such as Um Qais, Jerash, and Petra, while also harboring hidden ruins resting amongst the land.

Set like an oasis in the dramatic terrain, the location is easily accessible and defines the resort and spa experience in the Middle East - making it a destination of choice for those seeking the perfect retreat to relax and be pampered whilst enjoying the therapeutic benefits of Ma’In hot spring waterfalls.

name: Mujib Reserve
bio:
At 410 meters below sea level, the Mujib Biosphere Reserve is the lowest nature reserve on Earth. Its rugged and spectacular mountains border the Dead Sea coast and are dissected by several river-filled canyons that offer the best river and adventure hikes in Jordan. The breathtaking scenery and the challenge of negotiating Mujib’s fast-flowing rivers make the Reserve one of Jordan’s most popular natural attractions.

Mujib’s complex river system and all-year water flow enable it to support a rich biodiversity. To date, over 300 species of plants, 10 species of carnivores and numerous species of resident and migratory birds have been recorded. Some of the mountain and valley areas are difficult to reach and offer safe havens for rare species of cats, mountain goats (Ibex) and other mountain animals.

name: Shaumari Reserve
bio: Shaumari Wildlife Reserve was established in 1975 by the Royal Society for the Conservation of Nature as a breeding center for endangered or locally extinct wildlife. Today, following breeding programs with some of the world's leading wildlife parks and zoos, this small, 22-square-kilometre reserve is a thriving protected environment for some of the most rare species of animals in the Middle East. Oryx, ostriches, onagers (an Asian wild ass) and gazelles, which are depicted on many local 6th century Byzantine mosaics, are rebuilding their populations and reasserting their presence in this safe haven, protected from hunting and habitat destruction that nearly wiped them out.

name: Kan Zaman
bio:
Nestled on the hilltop of an old Jordanian village and enclosed within the stone walls of an ancient settlement is Kan Zamaan—Arabic for once upon a time. Kan Zamaan was once the focal point of Khirbet Abu Jaber, an isolated rural area developed by merchant brothers for farming and ranching. The impressive 19th century estate—dating back to Ottoman rule—served as an agricultural warehouse and a horse barn before succumbing to ruin.

The heritage estate’s 21st century renovation into a restaurant incorporates this golden past into the modern, perfectly balancing the old and new. Today, Kan Zamaan is a distinguished landmark that sheds a new light on its cultural and historic legacy, as it continues to delight local food lovers with its unique, authentic oriental and local cuisine garnished with forgotten flavors.

The restaurant’s stable transformed elegant dining room features a lavish Oriental spread alongside a wide selection of fine oriental cold and hot mezze, a signature center stage live chargrill for all of our mouthwatering chargrilled meats, and a selection of local inspired dishes. We also serve delectable grilled and salt baked fresh seafood, fresh bread, and signature clay roasted dishes. Our pastry chefs also prepare a selection of tempting desserts, boasting our one-of-a-kind live knafeh, prepared table side by our skilled chefs.

Oriental and local cuisine, authentic flavors, artisan food, art, music and culture; all find their home within the ancient walls of Kan Zamaan.

The legacy of once upon a time is now present…

bio:
A little history goes a long way. Back in 2015, Mohammad Mushtaha and Nasser Shehada crossed paths. Mohammad, a chef and foodie from Aqaba and Nasser, a young entrepreneur from Gaza. While sharing a plate of Shrimps on the coast of the beautiful Aqaba with their friends, they shared the dream of opening a restaurant and their love for Shrimps & Wings. Nasser's trip was over and he had to go back to Dubai, where he currently lives.

Mohammad and Nasser crossed paths again in a common friend's wedding in beginning of 2017. It was 3 days of festivities where they shared several plates of Shrimp. While eating a Shrimp, a light bulb moment happened; Mohammad and Nasser decided to make their dream come true.

It's been said that good things take time. Turns out great things take 5 months and 8 days, which is how long  it took them to build Shrimp Joint. Mohammad and Nasser shook hands and promised each other to follow one important rule and I quote:

name: Blue Fig
contact_person: Rola Al Mani, Basheer Habahbeh, Raed Dabes, Rola Almani
bio:
A TRIBUTE TO ALL THE CULTURES OF THE WORLD

The concept of BLUE FIG is brilliantly fueled by the synergy and richness of all the cultures coming together and celebrated under a brand. A fusion of concepts that ride heavily on creativity. BLUE FIG has built-in from within the concept "intrigue longevity". "Fads are built everyday and die as often", says founder Khalid S. Nahhas, "trends are set for substantially longer periods, but the triumphant engages a core substance beyond fads and trends, almost building a new culture". There is so much to offer by all cultures that one can never run out of intriguing diversity and compelling cross-cultural universality or commonalities. Ethnicity is a common denominator underlying the concept and driving its many natural colors.


UNIQUE DIVERSITY AND INTEGRATION

The integration of atmosphere, food, drink and cultural entertainment present a new "café culture". The BLUE FIG caters creatively to international clients, all day as well as evenings and late nights, through its diverse line of commodities and entertainment.


FUSION OF SPIRITS

The intangibles of the BLUE FIG such as the spirit, soul, theme, imagery and alternative literary ideas are manifested through the integration of all the "universal" previous tangibles. One can rely on finding literary works, intellectualism, and many alternative cultural entertainments at the BLUE FIG, continuously renewing itself and, in turn, the experiences of the "universal client".


CREATING A NEW DEMAND

Continuous Evolvement, Recreation, differentiation and innovation offering customers a wealth of options through "timeless moods", "improvised rituals of delight" and "engagement of all the senses".

name: La Calle
bio:
A simple yet lively Italian Restaurant & Pub that retains the ambiance of the old world and reflects the warmth & vitality which Italy is well-known for.

In the most traditional area of Jabal Amman, commonly known as the 1st Circle, one of the early 20th century shops has now been replaced by La Calle; an Italian Restaurant & Pub that retains the ambiance of the old world.

La Calle, a common Venetian word meaning ‘the narrow street’, is a simple yet lively place that reflects the warmth and vitality which Italy is well-known for. La Calle features a fascinatingly wide range of both Food & Beverage recipes from all over Italy, where traditional Italian ingredients are introduced but are carefully balanced with a range of family favorites in an effort to evoke the true taste of Italy.

name: Fred Astaire
bio:
Our Great Heritage

Fred Astaire co-founded our company in 1947 to establish a chain of studios under his name, ensuring that his techniques would be preserved and passed on to the public.  Our studios have produced a wealth of amateur and professional dancers who are living embodiments of Astaire’s style and grace.


Private, Group & Practice Lessons

The unique Fred Astaire teaching method is composed of private instruction, group lessons and practice lessons.  Regularly scheduled private instruction with one or two key teachers offering each student personalized attention, letting the student look and feel confident while developing the ability to lead or follow a partner.  Group lessons complement private instruction by applying patterns, technique and style.  Additionally, they allow the student the opportunity to meet others with similar dancing goals.  Finally, practice lessons link the information taught in private and group lessons.  Dancing is not only about learning steps, but performing in a live setting while adapting to different partners.  Practice lessons give teachers the ability to visualize a student’s developments and deliver a tailored approach to their private lessons. 


Parties 

Fred Astaire Dance Studios are always bustling with events and activities.  “Share the Experience” parties are routinely held at our studios where students can invite their friends and co-workers, who can then see for themselves how much the students enjoy dancing, and how well they are doing with their lessons.  Music and refreshments are available, and all have a good time. 


Programs

- Basic Lessons: All beginner students start with a series of basic lessons.  A limited number of step patterns are taught so a student can go out and begin to dance.  These lessons also help determine a student’s rate of learning and retention, interests and future potential.

- Social Foundation Program: Our first planned and personalized dance program customized to fit your lifestyle and dancing desires.  This program will add to your mastery of the basic elements of your social dances, allowing you to dance in any situation.  You will gain an understanding of footwork, an introduction to the various dance tempos, whether fast or slow, and the fundamentals of a good lead as a gentleman or following factors as a lady.  This program also provides an excellent stepping stone to our next level of instruction – the Bronze Trophy System.

- The Bronze Trophy Program: Designed for the person who wishes to become a good social dancer.  It is our most popular standard, and is the first Trophy Program available to new students.  Bronze dancers are considered fun to dance with in all the popular social dances.  They have complete confidence to dance a multitude of figures as well as have the styling, balance and control that creates an impressive appearance on the dance floor.

- The Silver Trophy Program: For those who wish to become exciting social dancers.  Silver dancers have the ability to impress others through their dance, are skilled in the art of expression, and can be distinguished by their versatility and style in all dances taught during their lessons.

- The Gold Trophy Program: For the person who wishes to become an excellent ballroom dancer.  Gold dancers have the ability to convey emotion through dance, not only to their partners but to others who are watching them.  These dancers will possess a complete and thorough knowledge of all major ballroom dances.

bio:

Paintball is one of the safest sports around; at the Jordan Paintball Club nothing is spared to insure your safety and enjoyment.

We pride ourselves on our unmatched safety track record. We also offer low impact paintball markers for kids and those who prefer to avoid the pain in paintball. All players are issued with full protection, including special goggles that cover the face and ears, neck protection, heavy duty camouflage outfits and an optional protective vest. We only use high quality paintballs of two different sizes, regular and small size. The paintballs themselves consists of a gelatin shell filled with food grade paint, which is also biodegradable.

name: Jordan Trail
bio:
The Jordan Trail is a long distance hiking trail in Jordan connecting the length of Jordan from Um Qais in the north to Aqaba in the south. Offering 40 days of hiking over more than 650 kilometers of trail, and travelling through 52 villages and towns on its way. The trail traverses the diverse landscapes and vistas of the country, from the rolling wooded hills of the north, the rugged wadis and cliffs overlooking the Jordan Rift Valley, the rose rock of Petra, the dramatic sands and towering mountains in Wadi Rum, to the crystal waters of the Red Sea.

 

As you walk the Jordan Trail, it becomes a journey through the history of Jordan and an encounter with its diverse culture. Travelling the length of the country enables a chance to peel through the different layers of culture, to taste the varied cuisines of Jordan, encounter locals while walking and spending your nights in their home-stays. It is also an opportunity to learn the history of Jordan, the different civilizations who have made their marks on the land. The trail moves through major historical sites in the region such as Um Qais, Jerash, and Petra, while also harboring hidden ruins resting amongst the land.

name: Sea Breeze Dive
bio:
Red Sand & Sea management realize that Aqaba's greatest asset is the Red Sea itself. Where residents  can experience some of the best snorkeling and diving spots , when you consider the rich variety of its underwater ecosystem. It is home to more than 1,200 species of fish, including 44 species of sharks. Nearly 20% of these are found only in the Red Sea. Divers can swim with brightly colored angelfish, butterflyfish and clownfish in addition to the Lost shipwreck spot and the Colorful coral reefs spots, the temperate climate and the gentle water currents have created a perfect environment for the growth of corals and a teeming plethora of marine life.

Knowing scuba diving has increased in recent decades to an extent that scuba diving and the business activity supporting it have become important tourism sectors stimulating a billion-dollar global industry, Sea Breeze Dive Club has been established in a PADI Dive Resort, the technical potential of our company consists of professional divers, who have the necessary licenses 
Our dive club is located at Alhamamat Altunisiyeh Street in the middle of Aqaba and (AL-Manara a luxury collection hotel Saraya Aqaba, Hyatt Regency Aqaba Ayla Resort, Intercontinental Aqaba Resort). We offer clean, superior, quality affordable scuba diving activities for outdoors men and women in Aqaba, Jordan.
We teach all range of PADI scuba diving courses, organize beach dives as well as boat dives for  certified divers and for those who never tried diving , Daily Diving Trip , furthermore we cater Snorkeling Boat Trip ,PADI Discovery Scuba Diving ,PADI Open Water Course E-Learning, PADI Advanced Open Water Course, PADI Rescue Diver Course , and PADI Divemaster Course

Calisthenics is a form of exercise consisting of a variety of gross motor movements; running, standing, grasping, pushing, etc. often performed rhythmically as bodyweight exercises. They are intended to increase body strength, body fitness, and flexibility, through movements such as pulling or pushing oneself up, bending, jumping, or swinging, using only one's body weight for resistance; usually conducted in concert with stretches.

name: Ma'in Hot Springs
bio:
Ma’In Hot Springs Resort & Spa is located 30 kilometres from the ‘mosaic’ city of Madaba and right of the corner of the Dead Sea. It is a scenic 60 minute drive from Amman Queen Alia International Airport (AMM). Lying 264 meters below sea level in a spectacular mountain landscape, Ma’In Hot Springs Resort & Spa is close by to the south-east corner of the Dead Sea and a leisurely drive to historic Madaba. It combines locally-inspired architecture and ambience with family friendly services, facilities and attention to detail.
Set like an oasis in the dramatic terrain, the location is easily accessible and defines the resort and spa experience in the Middle East - making it a destination of choice for those seeking the perfect retreat to relax and be pampered whilst enjoying the therapeutic benefits of Ma’In hot spring waterfalls.
The stunning property combines high levels of hospitality with locally - inspired architecture and peaceful surroundings to ensure an unforgettable experience. It offers a vast array of family friendly services and facilities to ensure personal attention in a welcoming atmosphere.

The resort features quality lodging, dining and an ever expanding list of outdoor activities ,which are available for visitors and overnight guests alike.

Mountain Breeze Resort is a firm favorite for families, travelers, weekenders and is a great venue for private and corporate events. It’s an escape from the fast-paced life of Amman city and a retreat into nature
